Description:
The Council is tendered and awarded a contract for Substance Misuse Services. The service is split into Lots as below;

Lot 1 - Barking and Dagenham Subwize Young People Integrated Substance Misuse (Drug and Alcohol) Service

Lot 2- Barking and Dagenham Adults Integrated Substance Misuse (Drug and Alcohol) Service

Brighton and Hove City Council and East Sussex County Council, in collaboration with the Office for the Sussex Police and Crime Commissioner, have awarded contracts for the following services:
Lot 1 - A Domestic Violence and Abuse Specialist Victim Support Service for Brighton and Hove;
Lot 2 - A Domestic Violence and Abuse Specialist Victim Support Service for East Sussex;
Lot 3 - A Rape and Sexual Violence Specialist Support Service across West Sussex, Brighton and Hove and East Sussex;
Lot 4 - A Stalking and Harassment Specialist Support Service across Brighton and Hove, East Sussex and West Sussex; and
Lot 5 - A Domestic Violence and Abuse Refuge and Strategic Partner for Brighton and Hove.
